readTree has many signatures, it can't be used as a functional interface.
If I wrap the call in a Supplier i need to try/catch the exceptions it throws:
if (parser.currentToken() != null) {
    Supplier<String> s = () -> {
        try {
            return MAPPER.readTree(tb.asParser()).toString();
        } catch (IOException e) {
            log.error("Failed to read content, Enricher: {}", name, e);
            return "";
        }
    };
    log.error("Enricher: {} failed on current token: {}, output to write: {}", name::toString,
          parser::currentToken, s::get);
}

